{"id": "50550", 
 "title": "Bug 50550: PropFind 404 error after MkCol success", 
 "description": "Bug 50550: PropFind 404 error after MkCol success. This issue seems to be related to caching. Note: This situation appears similar to call 21288 (FIXED: 'DirContext caching problem with Dreamweaver 6 when recursively creating directories'). This issue can be reproduced using a Jackrabbit client with the following code:

HttpClient client = new HttpClient();
String newDir = "http://localhost:8080/webdav/output/" + UUID.randomUUID() + "/";

// Comment out this request to make the second PropFind successful
HttpMethod propFindMethod1 = new PropFindMethod(newDir);
client.executeMethod(propFindMethod1);
propFindMethod1.releaseConnection();

HttpMethod mkcolMethod = new MkColMethod(newDir);
client.executeMethod(mkcolMethod);
mkcolMethod.releaseConnection();

HttpMethod propFindMethod = new PropFindMethod(newDir);
client.executeMethod(propFindMethod);
propFindMethod.releaseConnection();", 
 "OB": "A PropFind call on a resource returns a 404 error when executed after an MkCol for the same resource.", 
 "EB": "The MkCol request should be preceded by a PropFind request to trigger the issue.", 
 "SR": "To reproduce:
1. Execute a PropFind request on a specific resource.
2. Execute an MkCol request on the same resource.
3. Execute another PropFind request on the same resource.

Expected result: The second PropFind request should return a 404 error.

Note: In the access log, the first PropFind request followed by an MkCol request will show a 404 error for the second PropFind request. However, if the first PropFind request is omitted, the second PropFind request will be successful, as shown in the access log example provided."}
